<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-02-25T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-02-25T07:00:00-05:00" n="560" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6429: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-02-25T21:00:00+09:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            25, 1920—9 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received February 25—2
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>66. The Cabinet met yesterday and agreed to recommend to the
                                Diplomatic Advisory Council the gradual withdrawal of all Japanese
                                troops from Siberia. A meeting of the Council to consider this
                                recommendation will be held shortly.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>